Anthony O’BOYLE, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug FRANK, Cornell Steamboat Company, Claimant-Appellant, and Barge M. F. Phalen, Edward J. Phalen, Claimant-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 20, 1928. No. 164. Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hickox & Keating, of New York City (Eobert S. Erskine and Henry P. Elliott, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Maeklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for Anthony O’Boyle. Poley & Martin, of New York City (James A. Martin, of New York City, of counsel), for the Phalen.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and AU-GUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PEE CUEIAM.

Decree affirmed, with costs.
